column5: ive been asked the same question many times....my responce is  "have you ever hit a deer with your car?"  "NO!" they would reply  "your welcome" as i would walk away

Lew, Do you see many Bucks out your way? All we ever see is Doe's around here, but I did have a huge Buck jump out in front of me on Airport road last week! It was just at Dusk as expected.

Not too many Brian but every now & then one wanders thru the yard. I posted this picture a couple weeks back but he's the only buck I've seen this year.    It was nice here last evening just at sunset when I looked out the back window and there were 2 does and a youngun only 50' from the house and then they hung around the yard for about 10 minutes. Would been nice to get a picture but I didn't want to spook them.  Neighbor down the road told my wife the other day that she watched a wolf take down and kill a deer on Clear Lake right in front of her place.
Its after five oclock and its still light out , there getting longer .
